v0.0.4 2013-09-06T08:39:23
 - Release 0.0.4 [Ioan Rogers]
 - * Make sure README is checked in
   * Use multiple_inheritance for Git::CommitBuild, otherwise the release
   history
     gets confused, giving the latest changelog entry the complete history
   (like now!) [Ioan Rogers]
 - Add an option to omit authors
   
   Useful for instance if there is only one author anyway. [Jakob Voss]
 - [Closes #1] Get HEAD version from Git::Tag if available. Thanks to
   @jddurand for reporting [Ioan Rogers]
 - Don't run Test::Synopsis, the synopsis is an .ini file [Ioan Rogers]
 - Default to omitting author email. Don't group by author, instead add
   name to end of message. [Ioan Rogers]
 - Tags are now build-ready without Dist::Zilla [Ioan Rogers]
 - Require latest version of dzp::changelogfromgit to stop cpantester dep
   failures [Ioan Rogers]
 - Placeholder Changes to shut up dzp::git::commit [Ioan Rogers]
 - Revert dist.ini [Ioan Rogers]
 - Not being autocommitted [Ioan Rogers]
 - Testing github::update [Ioan Rogers]
 - Initial ReadmeMarkdownFromPod file [Ioan Rogers]
 - dzp::git doesn't use nextversion [Ioan Rogers]
 - Using all dzp::git [Ioan Rogers]
 - Allow dirty readme [Ioan Rogers]
 - Allow dirty readme [Ioan Rogers]
 - Commit any changes [Ioan Rogers]
 - Ignore readme [Ioan Rogers]
